        "username": "Olrac",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/olrac/{size}/22934_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-05T15:19:35.129Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Please consider supporting <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/exploring-official-bot-support-in-signal/54047/10\"><strong>this thread about official bot functionality in Signal</strong></a> and providing a documented API, instead of leaving developers to reverse-engineer private server endpoints.</p>\n<p>Telegram demonstrates that bots and one-way information channels can be implemented in a controlled, user-friendly way without compromising the core messaging experience. WhatsApp, on the other hand, forces companies into expensive and highly restricted backend workflows.</p>\n<p>An official Signal bot model with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>one-way information channels for offers and service notifications, and</li>\n<li>optional interactive bots via a supported API</li>\n</ul>\n<p>would remove the need for unofficial tooling, reduce security risks, and give the Signal Foundation a sustainable monetization option (for example via a lightweight per-message API fee).</p>\n<p>I believe this is a healthier long-term direction than pushing the community toward reverse-engineering private APIs.</p>",
